&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Older Adult Mental Health Services – Home Treatment for Older Adults&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based at New Haven – Bromsgrove&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical/Counselling Psychologist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 8a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;18.75 Hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have a permanent vacancy for a 0.5 WTE Band 8a Clinical or Counselling psychologist who is HCPC registered, to work in Worcestershire’s Older Adult Mental Health Services, based in Newhaven, Princess of Wales Community Hospital, Bromsgrove. This is an exciting opportunity to support a new specialist home treatment service for older people. The post holder will have experience of working with older people, across the range of mental health issues associated with ageing, including dementia. In addition to offering evidence based psychological therapies they would be supporting the teams in their ability to offer brief interventions, offering complex case discussions and using their skills in evaluation. Experience of supporting older adults in their transition from hospital and preventing admissions would be helpful. A psychology assistant will support them in the role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;There are four locality teams working across the county of Worcestershire, where psychology is a valued and integrated part of each team. There are also psychologists working in the inpatient service, Early Intervention Dementia Service and Neuropsychology. We are friendly team, CPD is actively encouraged and we have excellent links with the local Clinical Psychology training courses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information and an opportunity to informally discuss this position please contact Dr Andy Ashley, Lead for Psychological Interventions, Older Adult Mental Health and Specialist Community Care (Tel. 01527 488279 or email: Andrew.ashley@nhs.net) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
